    {
      "id": "9a32c707f2c1acb4ecb87989470c2685ce017316",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2021-08-13 16:47:23.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nI accidentally mis-clicked should be added back when the build finishes. \n\nNote that there are patches to parallelism configure which would be great to land, but they are blocked because they break Oleg's builders. It would be good to find a way to move forward with that (eg. make the parallel configure optional?) because configure really is a bottleneck in building. I think this patch will only help RPM builds that run configure multiple times (a similar one for Ubuntu would be nice), but not the initial run itself.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
